763  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_DIVIRQ, &prev, 1); /* read config */
764  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
765  {
766  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read divirq failed.\n"); /* read divirq failed */
767 
768  return 1; /* return error */
769  }
770  prev &= ~(1 << 7); /* clear the settings */
771  res = a_mfrc522_write(handle, MFRC522_REG_DIVIRQ, &prev, 1); /* write config */
772  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
773  {
774  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: write divirq failed.\n"); /* write divirq failed */
775 
776  return 1; /* return error */
777  }
778 
779  if ((prev1 & (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_TIMER)) != 0) /* timer */
780  {
781  handle->irq_flag |= 1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_TIMER; /* set the irq flag */
782  if (handle->receive_callback != NULL) /* if receive callback */
783  {
784  handle->receive_callback(MFRC522_INTERRUPT_TIMER); /* run callback */
785  }
786  }
787  if ((prev1 & (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_ERR)) != 0) /* err */
788  {
789  handle->irq_flag |= 1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_ERR; /* set the irq flag */
790  if (handle->receive_callback != NULL) /* if receive callback */
791  {
792  handle->receive_callback(MFRC522_INTERRUPT_ERR); /* run callback */
793  }
794  }
795  if ((prev1 & (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_LO_ALERT)) != 0) /* lo alert */
796  {
797  handle->irq_flag |= 1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_LO_ALERT; /* set the irq flag */
798  if (handle->receive_callback != NULL) /* if receive callback */
799  {
800  handle->receive_callback(MFRC522_INTERRUPT_LO_ALERT); /* run callback */
801  }
802  }
803  if ((prev1 & (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_HI_ALERT)) != 0) /* hi alert */
804  {
805  handle->irq_flag |= 1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_HI_ALERT; /* set the irq flag */
806  if (handle->receive_callback != NULL) /* if receive callback */
807  {
808  handle->receive_callback(MFRC522_INTERRUPT_HI_ALERT); /* run callback */
809  }
810  }
811  if ((prev1 & (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_IDLE)) != 0) /* idle */
812  {
813  handle->irq_flag |= 1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_IDLE; /* set the irq flag */
814  if (handle->receive_callback != NULL) /* if receive callback */
815  {
816  handle->receive_callback(MFRC522_INTERRUPT_IDLE); /* run callback */
817  }
818  }
819  if ((prev1 & (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_RX)) != 0) /* rx */
820  {
821  handle->irq_flag |= 1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_RX; /* set the irq flag */
822  if (handle->receive_callback != NULL) /* if receive callback */
823  {
824  handle->receive_callback(MFRC522_INTERRUPT_RX); /* run callback */
825  }
826  }
827  if ((prev1 & (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_TX)) != 0) /* tx */
828  {
829  handle->irq_flag |= 1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_TX; /* set the irq flag */
830  if (handle->receive_callback != NULL) /* if receive callback */
831  {
832  handle->receive_callback(MFRC522_INTERRUPT_TX); /* run callback */
833  }
834  }
835  if ((prev2 & (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT2_CRC)) != 0) /* crc */
836  {
837  handle->irq_flag |= 1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_CRC; /* set the irq flag */
838  if (handle->receive_callback != NULL) /* if receive callback */
839  {
840  handle->receive_callback(MFRC522_INTERRUPT_CRC); /* run callback */
841  }
842  }
843  if ((prev2 & (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT2_MFIN_ACT)) != 0) /* mfin act */
844  {
845  handle->irq_flag |= 1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_MFIN_ACT; /* set the irq flag */
846  if (handle->receive_callback != NULL) /* if receive callback */
847  {
848  handle->receive_callback(MFRC522_INTERRUPT_MFIN_ACT); /* run callback */
849  }
850  }
851  }
852 
853  return 0; /* success return 0 */
854 }

878 uint8_t mfrc522_transceiver(mfrc522_handle_t *handle,
879  mfrc522_command_t command,
880  uint8_t *in_buf, uint8_t in_len,
881  uint8_t *out_buf, uint8_t *out_len,
882  uint8_t *err, uint32_t ms)
883 {
884  uint8_t res;
885  uint8_t prev;
886  uint8_t i;
887  uint16_t wait_for;
888  uint32_t timeout;
889 
890  if (handle == NULL) /* check handle */
891  {
892  return 2; /* return error */
893  }
894  if (handle->inited != 1) /* check handle initialization */
895  {
896  return 3; /* return error */
897  }
898  if ((in_buf == NULL) || (out_buf == NULL)) /* check the buffer */
899  {
900  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: buffer is NULL.\n"); /* buffer is NULL */
901 
902  return 4; /* return error */
903  }
904  if (in_len > 64) /* check the length */
905  {
906  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: in_len is over 64.\n"); /* in_len is over 64 */
907 
908  return 5; /* return error */
909  }
910 
911  /* set idle */
912  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_COMMAND, &prev, 1); /* read config */
913  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
914  {
915  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read command failed.\n"); /* read command failed */
916 
917  return 1; /* return error */
918  }
919  prev &= ~(0xF << 0); /* clear the settings */
920  prev |= MFRC522_COMMAND_IDLE; /* set the idle */
921  res = a_mfrc522_write(handle, MFRC522_REG_COMMAND, &prev, 1); /* write config */
922  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
923  {
924  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: write command failed.\n"); /* write command failed */
925 
926  return 1; /* return error */
927  }
928 
929  /* flush the fifo */
930  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_FIFO_LEVEL, &prev, 1); /* read level */
931  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
932  {
933  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read fifo level failed.\n"); /* read fifo level failed */
934 
935  return 1; /* return error */
936  }
937  prev |= 1 << 7; /* set the flush bit */
938  res = a_mfrc522_write(handle, MFRC522_REG_FIFO_LEVEL, &prev, 1); /* write level */
939  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
940  {
941  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: write fifo level failed.\n"); /* write fifo level failed */
942 
943  return 1; /* return error */
944  }
945 
946  /* write fifo */
947  for (i = 0; i < in_len; i++) /* loop */
948  {
949  res = a_mfrc522_write(handle, MFRC522_REG_FIFO_DATA, in_buf + i, 1); /* write data */
950  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
951  {
952  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: write fifo data failed.\n"); /* write fifo data failed */
953 
954  return 1; /* return error */
955  }
956  }
957 
958  /* clear the flag */
959  handle->irq_flag = 0; /* clear the irq flag */
960  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_COMIRQ, &prev, 1); /* read config */
961  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
962  {
963  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read comirq failed.\n"); /* read comirq failed */
964 
965  return 1; /* return error */
966  }
967  prev &= ~(1 << 7); /* clear the settings */
968  res = a_mfrc522_write(handle, MFRC522_REG_COMIRQ, &prev, 1); /* write config */
969  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
970  {
971  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: write comirq failed.\n"); /* write comirq failed */
972 
973  return 1; /* return error */
974  }
975  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_DIVIRQ, &prev, 1); /* read config */
976  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
977  {
978  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read divirq failed.\n"); /* read divirq failed */
979 
980  return 1; /* return error */
981  }
982  prev &= ~(1 << 7); /* clear the settings */
983  res = a_mfrc522_write(handle, MFRC522_REG_DIVIRQ, &prev, 1); /* write config */
984  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
985  {
986  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: write divirq failed.\n"); /* write divirq failed */
987 
988  return 1; /* return error */
989  }
990 
991  /* set the command */
992  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_COMMAND, &prev, 1); /* read config */
993  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
994  {
995  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read command failed.\n"); /* read command failed */
996 
997  return 1; /* return error */
998  }
999  prev &= ~(0xF << 0); /* clear the settings */
1000  prev |= command; /* set the command */
1001  res = a_mfrc522_write(handle, MFRC522_REG_COMMAND, &prev, 1); /* write config */
1002  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
1003  {
1004  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: write command failed.\n"); /* write command failed */
1005 
1006  return 1; /* return error */
1007  }
1008 
1009  /* set bit framing */
1010  if (command == MFRC522_COMMAND_TRANSCEIVE) /* if transceive*/
1011  {
1012  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_BIT_FRAMING, &prev, 1); /* read bit framing */
1013  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
1014  {
1015  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read bit framing failed.\n"); /* read bit framing failed */
1016 
1017  return 1; /* return error */
1018  }
1019  prev |= 1 << 7; /* set the start bit */
1020  res = a_mfrc522_write(handle, MFRC522_REG_BIT_FRAMING, &prev, 1); /* write bit framing */
1021  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
1022  {
1023  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: write bit framing failed.\n"); /* write bit framing failed */
1024 
1025  return 1; /* return error */
1026  }
1027  }
1028 
1029  /* set the wait bit */
1030  if (command == MFRC522_COMMAND_MF_AUTHENT) /* if authent */
1031  {
1032  wait_for = (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_IDLE) |
1033  (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_TIMER); /* if idle && timer */
1034  }
1035  else if (command == MFRC522_COMMAND_TRANSCEIVE) /* if transceive */
1036  {
1037  wait_for = (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_RX) |
1038  (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_TIMER); /* if rx && timer */
1039  }
1040  else if (command == MFRC522_COMMAND_CALC_CRC) /* if crc */
1041  {
1042  wait_for = (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_CRC) |
1043  (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_TIMER); /* if crc && timer */
1044  }
1045  else
1046  {
1047  wait_for = (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_IDLE) |
1048  (1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_TIMER); /* if idle && timer */
1049  }
1050  timeout = ms; /* set timeout */
1051  while (timeout != 0) /* check the timeout */
1052  {
1053  handle->delay_ms(1); /* delay 1ms */
1054  timeout--; /* timeout-- */
1055  if ((handle->irq_flag & wait_for) != 0) /* check the wait for */
1056  {
1057  break; /* break */
1058  }
1059  if (timeout == 0) /* if timeout == 0 */
1060  {
1061  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read timeout.\n"); /* read timeout */
1062 
1063  return 6; /* return error */
1064  }
1065  }
1066 
1067  /* end */
1068  if (command == MFRC522_COMMAND_TRANSCEIVE) /* if transceive*/
1069  {
1070  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_BIT_FRAMING, &prev, 1); /* read bit framing */
1071  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
1072  {
1073  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read bit framing failed.\n"); /* read bit framing failed */
1074 
1075  return 1; /* return error */
1076  }
1077  prev &= ~(1 << 7); /* clear the settings */
1078  res = a_mfrc522_write(handle, MFRC522_REG_BIT_FRAMING, &prev, 1); /* write bit framing */
1079  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
1080  {
1081  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: write bit framing failed.\n"); /* write bit framing failed */
1082 
1083  return 1; /* return error */
1084  }
1085  }
1086 
1087  /* check timer timeout */
1088  if ((handle->irq_flag & ((1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_TIMER))) != 0) /* check the timer */
1089  {
1090  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: timer timeout.\n"); /* timer timeout */
1091 
1092  return 7; /* return error */
1093  }
1094 
1095  /* check error */
1096  if ((handle->irq_flag & ((1 << MFRC522_INTERRUPT_ERR))) != 0) /* check the error */
1097  {
1098  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_ERROR, err, 1); /* read config */
1099  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
1100  {
1101  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read error failed.\n"); /* read error failed */
1102 
1103  return 1; /* return error */
1104  }
1105  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: find error.\n"); /* find error */
1106 
1107  return 8; /* return error */
1108  }
1109 
1110  /* get the fifo */
1111  if ((command == MFRC522_COMMAND_TRANSCEIVE) && ((*out_len) != 0)) /* if transceive and need get from fifo */
1112  {
1113  uint8_t level;
1114 
1115  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_FIFO_LEVEL, &level, 1); /* read level */
1116  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
1117  {
1118  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read fifo level failed.\n"); /* read fifo level failed */
1119 
1120  return 1; /* return error */
1121  }
1122 
1123  *out_len = level > (*out_len) ? (*out_len) : level; /* set the output length */
1124  for (i = 0; i < (*out_len); i++) /* loop */
1125  {
1126  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_FIFO_DATA, out_buf + i, 1); /* read data */
1127  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
1128  {
1129  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read fifo data failed.\n"); /* read fifo data failed */
1130 
1131  return 1; /* return error */
1132  }
1133  }
1134  }
1135  if ((command == MFRC522_COMMAND_MEM) && ((*out_len) != 0)) /* if mem and need get from fifo */
1136  {
1137  uint8_t level;
1138 
1139  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_FIFO_LEVEL, &level, 1); /* read level */
1140  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
1141  {
1142  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read fifo level failed.\n"); /* read fifo level failed */
1143 
1144  return 1; /* return error */
1145  }
1146  *out_len = level > (*out_len) ? (*out_len) : level; /* set the output length */
1147  for (i = 0; i < (*out_len); i++) /* loop */
1148  {
1149  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_FIFO_DATA, out_buf + i, 1); /* read data */
1150  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
1151  {
1152  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read fifo data failed.\n"); /* read fifo data failed */
1153 
1154  return 1; /* return error */
1155  }
1156  }
1157  }
1158 
1159  /* stop the timer */
1160  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_CONTROL, &prev, 1); /* read control */
1161  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
1162  {
1163  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read control failed.\n"); /* read control failed */
1164 
1165  return 1; /* return error */
1166  }
1167  prev |= 1 << 7; /* set the stop bit */
1168  res = a_mfrc522_write(handle, MFRC522_REG_CONTROL, &prev, 1); /* write control */
1169  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
1170  {
1171  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: write control failed.\n"); /* write control failed */
1172 
1173  return 1; /* return error */
1174  }
1175 
1176  /* set the idle */
1177  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_COMMAND, &prev, 1); /* read config */
1178  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
1179  {
1180  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: read command failed.\n"); /* read command failed */
1181 
1182  return 1; /* return error */
1183  }
1184  prev &= ~(0xF << 0); /* clear the settings */
1185  prev |= MFRC522_COMMAND_IDLE; /* set the idle */
1186  res = a_mfrc522_write(handle, MFRC522_REG_COMMAND, &prev, 1); /* write config */
1187  if (res != 0) /* check the result */
1188  {
1189  handle->debug_print("mfrc522: write command failed.\n"); /* write command failed */
1190 
1191  return 1; /* return error */
1192  }
1193  *err = prev; /* set the 0 */
1194 
1195  return 0; /* success return 0 */
1196 }

1418 uint8_t mfrc522_get_command(mfrc522_handle_t *handle, mfrc522_command_t *command)
1419 {
1420  uint8_t res;
1421  uint8_t prev;
1422 
1423  if (handle == NULL) /* check handle */
1424  {
1425  return 2; /* return error */
1426  }
1427  if (handle->inited != 1) /* check handle initialization */
1428  {
1429  return 3; /* return error */
1430  }
1431 
1432  res = a_mfrc522_read(handle, MFRC522_REG_COMMAND, &prev, 1); /* read config */
